<HL>
   BP Petroleum to Sell Funk
</HL>
<DATE>
06/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   BP
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   LONDON -- BP Nutrition Inc., a unit of British Petroleum
Co., said it is offering its Edward J. Funk &amp; Sons Inc. unit
for sale.
   Edward J. Funk &amp; Sons produces and markets corn and
soybean seed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Robin Gourlay, chief executive of BP Nutrition, said the
company's strategy "is to pursue opportunities in our
traditional businesses while shifting the balance of our
portfolio towards value-added products and the final
consumer."
</TEXT>
